This paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of machine learning (cs.LG) as it deals with the training of Generative Adversarial Networks (GANs) and the choice of loss function. It also involves computer vision (cs.CV) as GANs are commonly used for image generation. Additionally, it may fall under the sub-categories of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) as GANs are a popular topic in these fields. Finally, it could also be categorized under graphics (cs.GR) as GANs are often used for generating realistic images and videos.
